  "prompt": "When is it likely that the proposed extended maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks will be implemented for private sectors in India?",
  "response": "As of my last update in October 2023, the extension of maternity leave from 12 to 26 weeks in India, which applies to the private sector, was already implemented with the passage of the Maternity Benefit (Amendment) Act in 2017. This law mandates that women employed in the private sector are entitled to 26 weeks of paid maternity leave. If you are referring to any new proposals or adjustments beyond this, I recommend checking the latest government announcements or reputable news sources for the most current information, as legislative processes and policy implementations can evolve.",
